    "narrativeArc": "The video explains how women fall in love by breaking down the 'process' into 'two key factors': Time and Investment. It uses analogies (barbecue brisket, instant ramen) and visual metaphors (graphs, flowcharts, climbing stairs) to illustrate concepts. It then details three forms of investment: Compliance (requests, demands, taken), Mental Rumination (tasks, mystery, anger), and Temporal Investment (spending time). The video progresses from defining concepts to providing actionable advice, highlighting common mistakes men make, and emphasizing the importance of gradual escalation and understanding female psychology. It concludes with a summary of the investment-over-time model and an advertisement for a related course."
